{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781418880,"nonce":"gRb1ZtLGwcSFF6lahxaAVfO0raE=","title":"A struct-level composite unique attribute `#[unique(col_a, col_b)]` is accepted by the `Table` derive (compiles with no error) but produces **no** `UNIQUE` constraint in the generated DDL.","message":"```rust\nstruct Repository\u003c'scope, C: ColumnMode = ColumnExpr\u003e {\n    #[column(primary_key, db_type = \"uuid\")]\n    id: C::Type\u003c'scope, uuid::Uuid\u003e,\n    #[column(db_type = \"uuid\")]\n    organization_id: C::Type\u003c'scope, uuid::Uuid\u003e,\n    slug: C::Type\u003c'scope, String\u003e,\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n`squealy_model::script::\u003cCatalogDb, Postgres\u003e(\u0026Postgres)` renders:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE \"catalog\".\"repositorys\" (\n  \"id\" uuid NOT NULL,\n  \"organization_id\" uuid NOT NULL,\n  \"slug\" text NOT NULL,\n  -- ...\n  CONSTRAINT \"pk_repositorys\" PRIMARY KEY (\"id\")\n);\n```\n\nNo `uq_...` constraint for `(organization_id, slug)`.\n\n\nEither emit the composite unique constraint, e.g.\n\n```sql\nCONSTRAINT \"uq_repositorys_organization_id_slug\" UNIQUE (\"organization_id\", \"slug\")\n```\n\nor — if struct-level `#[unique(...)]` is not a supported attribute — fail the derive with a clear \"unknown attribute\" error rather than silently ignoring it.\n\n\nSingle-column `#[column(unique)]` works (it emits `uq_organizations_slug`, `uq_users_email`, etc.). It is specifically the composite / table-level form that is silently dropped.\n\n\nEnforce `(organization, slug)` uniqueness in application code (check-then-insert).","files":null}]}